le the case where `app-user` might already exist, either by checking first or using `updateUser` as a fallback if creation fails.\n\nWriting the mongosh script... The `aggregate` operation in MongoDB requires `find` privileges on the collection, so granting `find` on `appdb.reports` should be sufficient for the `reportingRole`. Even though `readonly-user` already has broad read access to all collections in `appdb` through the `read` role, the task specifically requires this custom role to exist and be assigned, so I need to define what actions it should include for the aggregate operation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":36559,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf8be85b-a276-4653-be19-21bd9c99fc1b","uuid":"6f4de475-1a4b-450e-a203-81873fc51354","request_id":"req_011Cc8695uU1dLw36cw91dYB"}
